Las Vegas is surrounded by public land, yet this particular POTA park near Las Vegas sees surprisingly low activation numbers. Is it RF noise? Accessibility? Competition with more popular parks? Or is it simply hidden in plain sight?

As a POTA activator, I visit the park, look at the terrain, consider band conditions, and talk through the real-world reasons why this park may be skipped by many operators. snippet.title: Texas POTA at Lake Ray Roberts | New Record & Huge Pileups

Lake Ray Roberts is one of my favorite local activation spots, but this one didn’t come without its challenges. For this activation, I’m running the IC-7300 MkII on 20m phone and putting it through a true portable test out in a Texas state park where conditions are always changing.

That’s what I love about POTA. Every activation is different. Every park teaches you something new.

AI replacing human jobs---
---------Summary:
New amendments will establish the groundwork for enabling online renewal or replacement of a B.C. driver’s licence, BCID, and photo BC Service Cards through ICBC’s website
The new process will save people time and reduce trips to ICBC offices, freeing up space for other in-person appointments

Online services will particularly benefit people in rural and remote communities. Proposed amendments to the Motor Vehicle Act will enable ICBC to renew or replace driver's licences, BC Identification (BCID), and photo BC Service Cards online, saving people time. snippet.title: RUBBISH ANTENNA SERIES Ep.2 — Swinging Farm Gates… Will This Actually Work?!
snippet.description:
📡 Welcome to Episode 2 of the Rubbish Antenna Series (RAS)

— where we turn everyday objects into real working HF radio antennas.

In this episode…

I attempt something completely ridiculous:

👉 Using a FARM GATE as an antenna.

This absolutely should not work.

But radio has a funny way of surprising us.

⚠️ This build used whatever was available on-site — including a tuner.

🔥 Watch right to the end…

Because from THIS episode forward, the RAS rules are changing in a big way.

⸻

🚨 ELECTRIC FENCE / LIVE STRUCTURE WARNING

⚠️ IMPORTANT SAFETY WARNING

🚫 NEVER — under ANY circumstances — connect radio equipment to an electrified fence, live electrical structure, or anything that may carry voltage.

Electric fences, power lines, metal infrastructure, and unknown metal objects can carry dangerous or lethal current — even if they appear inactive.

⚠️ This demonstration was performed only on metal structures that were verified to be completely de-energized and safe.

If you are not 100% certain a structure is safe:

👉 DO NOT TOUCH IT
👉 DO NOT CONNECT TO IT
👉 DO NOT ATTEMPT THIS

Your safety comes first.

⸻

🌏 WHY THIS SERIES EXISTS

The Rubbish Antenna Series explores real-world improvisation when normal antennas aren’t available — especially in remote or emergency situations where communication can be critical.

⸻

🔋 Powered in the field by VTOMAN

⸻

📡 Subscribe for the next RAS episode — things are about to get wild.

snippet.title: Trump cede ante gas: Shell avanza en Campo Dragón
snippet.description:
La geopolítica energética acaba de dar un giro incómodo: Shell confirma que la licencia general de EE.UU. para exploración en Venezuela permitirá avanzar con el proyecto gasífero en Campo Dragón, un yacimiento con reservas estimadas de hasta 4,5 billones de pies cúbicos. Lo que durante años fue bloqueado por sanciones, ahora se reabre cuando el mercado energético aprieta y el Caribe necesita gas para sostener su industria.
La propia compañía admitió a Reuters que la emisión de licencias es “una señal positiva” que habilita el proyecto, evidenciando que la política de presión de Washington convive con excepciones estratégicas cuando el suministro global lo exige. Mientras tanto, Trinidad y Tobago busca alimentar la planta Atlantic LNG, golpeada por la escasez de gas.

snippet.title: Denk Mountain SOTA Activation – KX2 + AX1 Ultra-Portable Summit Setup
snippet.description:
